<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1606,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Remarks.â€”The petition to the International Commission of Zoological Nomenclature (ICZN) asking to retain usage of the 
<taxonomicName authority="(Marshall et al. 2018 a)" baseAuthorityName="Marshall" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[277,696,1642,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platypleurini">
Platypleurini (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, D. C. &amp; Moulds, M. &amp; Boulard, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Ewart, A. &amp; Wei, C. &amp; Mirathe, K. &amp; Popple, L. W. &amp; Price, B. W. &amp; Simon, C." box="[439,687,1642,1668]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="49 - 54" refId="ref69467" refString="Marshall, D. C., Moulds, M., Boulard, M., Sanborn, A. F., Ewart, A., Wei, C., Mirathe, K., Popple, L. W., Price, B. W. &amp; Simon, C. (2018 a) Case 3761 - Platypleurini Schmidt, 1918: proposed precedence over HAMZARIA Distant, 1905 to conserve nomenclatural stability in the CICADIDAE (Insecta: Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: CICADOIDEA). Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature, 75, 49 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.21805 / bzn. v 75. a 012" type="journal article" year="2018">Marshall et al. 2018a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was recently supported (ICZN 2020). 
<bibRefCitation author="Price, B. W." box="[1146,1288,1642,1668]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref70327" refString="Price, B. W. (2010) Historical biogeography of the tribe Platypleurini Schmidt, 1918 (Hemiptera: Cicadidae), with a focus on southern Africa. Ph. D. dissertation, Rhodes University, Grahamstown, 133 pp." type="book" year="2010">Price (2010)</bibRefCitation>
performed a genetic analysis that showed the 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1905 a" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[518,784,1678,1705]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hamzini">
Hamzini 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[622,784,1678,1705]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="379 - 387" refId="ref68243" refString="Distant, W. L. (1905 a) Rhynchotal notes XXXI. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 7, 15, 379 - 387. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03745480509443064" type="journal article" year="1905">Distant, 1905a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
placed deep within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1199,1678,1704]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platypleurini">Platypleurini</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, Y. J." box="[1209,1333,1678,1704]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="59 - 81" refId="ref69341" refString="Lee, Y. J. (2014) Cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Laos, with the description of four new genera and two new species. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.): International Journal of Entomology, 50, 59 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2014.934038" type="journal article" year="2014">Lee (2014)</bibRefCitation>
formally synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[308,453,1714,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platypleurini">Platypleurini</taxonomicName>
into 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[510,606,1714,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hamzini">Hamzini</taxonomicName>
based on the principle of priority and the data in 
<bibRefCitation author="Price, B. W." box="[1162,1305,1714,1740]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref70327" refString="Price, B. W. (2010) Historical biogeography of the tribe Platypleurini Schmidt, 1918 (Hemiptera: Cicadidae), with a focus on southern Africa. Ph. D. dissertation, Rhodes University, Grahamstown, 133 pp." type="book" year="2010">Price (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Price, B. W. &amp; Marshall, D. C. &amp; Barker, N. P. &amp; Simon, C. &amp; Villet, M. H." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="842 - 861" refId="ref70372" refString="Price, B. W., Marshall, D. C., Barker, N. P., Simon, C. &amp; Villet, M. H. (2019) Out of Africa? A dated molecular phylogeny of the cicada tribe Platypleurini Schmidt (Hemiptera: Cicadidae), with a focus on the genus Platypleura Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville. Systematic Entomology, 44, 842 - 861. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12360" type="journal article" year="2019">
Price 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[393,489,1750,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hamzini">Hamzini</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[557,702,1750,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platypleurini">Platypleurini</taxonomicName>
based on the application to the ICZN. Orapini also was made a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[365,510,1786,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platypleurini">Platypleurini</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Price, B. W. &amp; Marshall, D. C. &amp; Barker, N. P. &amp; Simon, C. &amp; Villet, M. H." box="[552,757,1786,1812]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="842 - 861" refId="ref70372" refString="Price, B. W., Marshall, D. C., Barker, N. P., Simon, C. &amp; Villet, M. H. (2019) Out of Africa? A dated molecular phylogeny of the cicada tribe Platypleurini Schmidt (Hemiptera: Cicadidae), with a focus on the genus Platypleura Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville. Systematic Entomology, 44, 842 - 861. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12360" type="journal article" year="2019">
Price 
<emphasis box="[616,665,1786,1812]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1606,2028]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<bibRefCitation author="Price, B. W. &amp; Marshall, D. C. &amp; Barker, N. P. &amp; Simon, C. &amp; Villet, M. H." box="[199,407,1822,1848]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="842 - 861" refId="ref70372" refString="Price, B. W., Marshall, D. C., Barker, N. P., Simon, C. &amp; Villet, M. H. (2019) Out of Africa? A dated molecular phylogeny of the cicada tribe Platypleurini Schmidt (Hemiptera: Cicadidae), with a focus on the genus Platypleura Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville. Systematic Entomology, 44, 842 - 861. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12360" type="journal article" year="2019">
Price 
<emphasis box="[265,316,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
performed a multi-gene analysis of the tribe. They showed that several genera were polyphyletic and some of these have already been grouped into new genera (Sanborn 2020). The 
<collectingCountry box="[1212,1347,1858,1884]" name="Madagascar" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
species included in the analysis formed a distinct branch. Further analyses of additional genera are necessary to determine if all genera represented in 
<collectingCountry box="[460,595,1930,1956]" name="Madagascar" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
diverge from a single ancestral group or if multiple colonization events of the island occurred.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1606,2028]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,321]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[249,394,2002,2028]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platypleurini">Platypleurini</taxonomicName>
are characterized by a vertically compressed body, head being about as wide or narrower than the mesonotum, eyes that do not protrude laterally, antennae with eight segments, lateral margins of the pronotum dilated and wider than the head, fore wings hyaline or opaque, generally with maculation, fore wing precostal area dilated, fore wings and hind wings with eight and six apical cells respectively, large timbal covers completely or almost enclosing the timbal cavity and extending anteriorly to metathorax, pygofer distal shoulder rounded, upper pygofer lobe absent, basal pygofer lobe developed, and digitate uncus (
<bibRefCitation author="Moulds, M. S." box="[947,1103,294,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="375 - 446" refId="ref70138" refString="Moulds, M. S. (2005) An appraisal of the higher classification of cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea) with special reference to the Australian fauna. Records of the Australian Museum, 57, 375 - 446. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.57.2005.1447" type="journal article" year="2005">Moulds 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
